課程概述 Course Description
       1. Crystal structure 2. Crystal bonding 3. Defects 4. Mechanical properties 5. Failure 6.Metals, CeramicsWhat constitute ‘material’- starting with atom and nucleus. Introduce the conventional teaching and point out the problem with these teaching. Introduce the missing link, ‘Covalent’ bond and show how it will help us understand many experimental facts we face.
Wherever possible actual experimental evidence will be presented in the class to back up the theoretical arguments.
    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
Introducing the difference of three kinds of bondingsThe relationship between the bondings and the crystal structure, mechanical propertiesUnderstand the experimental fact with the colvent bond 

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1 Bonding Theory for Metals & Alloys2 Bonding Theory for Metals & AlloysMiscibility Gap (MG) Between Two Liquid Metals3 Bonding Theory for Metals & AlloysMiscibility Gap (MG) Between Two Liquid Metals4Phase Equilibrium Diagrams5Phase Equilibrium Diagrams6Phase Equilibrium Diagrams7Phenomenon of Melting8Phenomenon of Melting9Midterm Exam10Superconductivity11Superconductivity12Nitinol; A Metal-Alloy with Memory13Nitinol; A Metal-Alloy with Memory14Mechanical Properties15Mechanical Properties16Summary of the Bonding Theory17Summary of the Bonding Theory18Final Exam 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


